1
00:00:10,897 --> 00:00:37,698
so we can start the standing meditation it takes about 10 to 15 minutes and if that's too long for you we'll just sit down so standing make sure you feel grounded balanced lifting up through the spine to the top of the head

2
00:00:40,479 --> 00:01:08,849
standing tall spend a moment now relaxing the brow eyes looking downward unfocused the jaw is there any tension there

3
00:01:11,344 --> 00:01:21,281
If so, just waggle it about a bit or clench the jaw and relax.

4
00:01:21,302 --> 00:01:21,903
Shoulders.

5
00:01:25,248 --> 00:01:26,191
Any tension there?

6
00:01:27,933 --> 00:01:29,656
If so, give them a good squeeze.

7
00:01:38,293 --> 00:01:41,477
Hands joined in front or by the side, whatever's comfortable.

8
00:01:47,686 --> 00:01:49,989
So just acknowledge the posture.

9
00:01:52,012 --> 00:01:54,656
Energy running up the spine to the top of the head.

10
00:01:55,596 --> 00:01:57,138
Everything else just hanging off.

11
00:01:58,040 --> 00:01:58,581
Relax.

12
00:02:06,120 --> 00:02:08,425
Draw your attention now to the soles of your feet.

13
00:02:08,844 --> 00:02:10,067
What can you feel down there?

14
00:02:15,134 --> 00:02:18,400
Can you isolate the sensations of pressure?

15
00:02:26,992 --> 00:02:31,199
Can you isolate the sensations of warmth or coolness?

16
00:02:39,701 --> 00:02:43,324
What about the more subtle sensations that tell you what you're standing on?

17
00:02:43,846 --> 00:02:46,848
The sponginess of carpets, the hardness of wood?

18
00:03:00,080 --> 00:03:04,443
Can you isolate areas of the souls where the sensations are neutral?

19
00:03:07,826 --> 00:03:09,709
Can you get in contact with those?

20
00:03:11,056 --> 00:03:32,912
around the instep maybe becoming aware of how the sensations are continuously changing as the body rebalances itself the body rebalances itself

21
00:03:40,552 --> 00:03:45,000
and just acknowledge that these sensations arise whether we want them to or not.

22
00:03:45,520 --> 00:03:48,064
They're not under our direct control.

23
00:04:00,245 --> 00:04:01,247
So let's take our time.

24
00:04:01,548 --> 00:04:07,336
Let's come up the body, see what we can feel both on the surface and the inside of the body.

25
00:04:08,481 --> 00:04:12,568
and be aware of areas that seem to be devoid of feeling, just empty.

26
00:04:34,502 --> 00:04:38,737
When you get to the abdomen, can you feel the sensations caused by the breath there?

27
00:04:40,120 --> 00:04:41,444
The rise and fall?

28
00:04:47,023 --> 00:04:48,005
Is there any tension?

29
00:05:02,785 --> 00:05:06,591
coming up into the stomach area can you feel the breath there?

30
00:05:07,992 --> 00:05:08,874
is it more prominent?

31
00:05:15,904 --> 00:05:16,966
is there any tension there?

32
00:05:29,324 --> 00:05:31,088
moving up into the chest

33
00:05:32,771 --> 00:05:33,892
Can you feel the breath there?

34
00:05:37,276 --> 00:05:38,237
Is that more prominent?

35
00:05:39,238 --> 00:05:40,420
Do you have a shallow breath?

36
00:05:47,509 --> 00:05:48,290
Any tensions?

37
00:06:00,764 --> 00:06:01,665
Feel the heartbeat?

38
00:06:15,127 --> 00:06:16,468
Shoulders still relaxed.

39
00:06:24,136 --> 00:06:24,637
The jaw.

40
00:06:31,882 --> 00:06:32,463
The brow.

41
00:06:32,504 --> 00:06:43,374
When you get to the scalp, scan it like you did the soles of your feet.

42
00:06:43,713 --> 00:06:44,814
What can you feel up there?

43
00:07:00,690 --> 00:07:21,432
now without moving your eyes just become aware of the colors and shapes ahead of you any sounds

44
00:07:28,365 --> 00:07:35,673
If you're in a quiet room, it might just be the sound of the electrical equipment in your body humming in your ears.

45
00:07:51,692 --> 00:07:53,935
What's the atmosphere of the room you're in like?

46
00:08:04,528 --> 00:08:07,879
Can you sense the presence of those around you or near you?

47
00:08:16,584 --> 00:08:18,791
So your attention is completely out there.

48
00:08:34,684 --> 00:09:01,501
now at the same time bring in the in here the feet the breath sensations in the body both inside and outside this is the bubble of our consciousness this is the world we are actually experiencing moment after moment being created by this complex organism

49
00:09:03,270 --> 00:09:05,673
We can't get outside it, underneath it, above it.

50
00:09:06,654 --> 00:09:07,115
This is it.

51
00:09:08,618 --> 00:09:10,721
This is the world as we experience it.

52
00:09:11,160 --> 00:09:12,783
This is our universe.

53
00:09:14,085 --> 00:09:15,767
And we're always at the centre of it.

54
00:09:22,755 --> 00:09:23,857
So we may as well relax.

55
00:09:25,639 --> 00:09:28,923
Relax into this present moment, wide awake.

56
00:09:30,827 --> 00:09:34,275
And just allow the attention to move to whatever draws it.

57
00:09:34,996 --> 00:09:38,686
Something you see, now something you hear, now something you feel.

58
00:09:39,206 --> 00:09:41,832
Just hang loose within that globe.

59
00:10:20,407 --> 00:10:45,537
relaxing abiding in the present moment wide awake in this mode just being we can let go of ideas of achieving something that's doing doing something now for some future result but here in this mode just being this is the result there's no reason for being it just is

60
00:11:22,202 --> 00:11:50,639
relaxing dwelling in the present moment wide awake in this mode just being there's only this ever-presenting moment there's no past there's no future just this moment here and now so there's no reason to plan even looking forward to anything doesn't matter we're not going anywhere in this mode

61
00:11:51,716 --> 00:11:53,086
We're always arriving.

62
00:12:29,787 --> 00:12:57,634
relaxing inhabiting the present moment wide awake in this mode we're sitting back within ourselves we're not reacting not responding just watching feeling experiencing and the world is just arising and passing away because we're not engaged we don't have to present some body be a person a personality

63
00:12:59,014 --> 00:13:00,452
We can be anonymous.

64
00:13:28,580 --> 00:13:39,037
relaxing, abiding in the present moment, wide awake, achieving nothing, going nowhere, being nobody.

65
00:13:39,076 --> 00:13:47,029
In this mode, we're developing five of the seven factors that lead to liberation.

66
00:13:48,312 --> 00:13:55,043
There's the awareness, of course, and there is that steadiness of attention, a phrase I prefer,

67
00:13:56,153 --> 00:14:18,162
concentration which i think makes us feel tight it's just the effort needed to maintain steadiness of attention a sense of calmness in that steadiness even if the body feels restless and the heart agitated the watcher the observer is calm

68
00:14:20,572 --> 00:14:22,754
And then there's the quality of equanimity.

69
00:14:22,794 --> 00:14:28,943
The dictionary says this is a balanced mind, but it should be a balanced mind and heart.

70
00:14:30,265 --> 00:14:35,312
Just letting go of holding on to views and opinions, be completely open-minded.

71
00:14:36,695 --> 00:14:44,746
And the heart, to let go of its prejudices, its fears, its aversions, its preferences, open-hearted.

72
00:14:44,767 --> 00:14:49,092
Open-hearted and open-minded.

73
00:14:52,769 --> 00:15:05,368
When these are established, we can bring in that curiosity specifically around the three characteristics of existence, impermanence, how we create suffering and not self.

74
00:15:06,590 --> 00:15:07,610
So this is the base.

75
00:15:08,432 --> 00:15:11,837
You can always return to it in sitting and in daily life.

76
00:15:14,442 --> 00:15:20,110
And in daily life to maintain this poise stops us from being carried away by emotions.

77
00:15:21,575 --> 00:15:31,886
You've had a phone call, you've finished a piece of work, you've been out and about and you feel anxious, irritated, overexcited.

78
00:15:32,267 --> 00:15:45,903
But if you can just stop after every action, after every piece of work, after every conversation and let the heart empty itself, then in the clarity and calmness, you can see the next intention.

79
00:15:47,424 --> 00:15:51,109
We can decide whether it's wholesome or skillful or otherwise.

80
00:15:53,350 --> 00:16:01,481
If it is unwholesome and unskillful, we just stay still with that energy until it dies away, or at least begins to die away.

81
00:16:02,744 --> 00:16:04,667
And so it doesn't have such a hold on us.

82
00:16:05,687 --> 00:16:07,691
If it's skillful, of course, we empower it.

83
00:16:09,514 --> 00:16:15,423
Just in this very simple way, we can better our habits and improve our personalities.

84
00:16:16,464 --> 00:16:18,447
But it takes this degree of attention.

85
00:16:22,813 --> 00:16:25,037
Our next intention is to sit.

86
00:16:26,918 --> 00:16:36,552
So let us now begin to practice in the way the Mahasi Sayadaw would have us by slowing everything down and becoming aware of the tiniest movements.

87
00:16:38,754 --> 00:16:50,070
We can begin to use noting words to keep the attention tethered to the object and stop it wandering off into fantasies, moving, stretching, lifting, placing, lowering.

88
00:16:51,889 --> 00:17:01,207
taking our time, aware of all the movements it takes to get this body into a sitting posture, intending to sit.

89
00:18:02,983 --> 00:18:31,252
make sure the posture is the expression of the awakened one like a good statue lift up from the lower abdomen the muscles in the lower back when you do this you will feel the breath in the abdomen much more clearly and then lift up the spine to the top of the head spend the initial moments relaxing the brow

90
00:18:35,586 --> 00:18:58,506
eyes gently closed, the jaw, shoulders, and hands on your lap, whatever feels comfortable.

91
00:19:05,032 --> 00:19:14,684
acknowledging the posture, energized up the spine, everything else relaxed.

92
00:19:14,704 --> 00:19:22,775
If in our sitting the body begins to slump, just make the intention, intending to lift, lifting, lifting.

93
00:19:23,736 --> 00:19:31,125
If the body becomes tense, intending to relax, relaxing, relaxing.

94
00:19:41,602 --> 00:20:11,490
draw the attention now to the breath of the abdomen or whatever you feel it most using a noting word rising rising falling falling if you're established at the nostrils and don't want to move to the abdomen in in out out get in touch with the breath the feel of it just relax the attention onto those feelings

95
00:22:56,625 --> 00:23:03,122
If the mind is wandering, when you wake up out of it, really recognize and acknowledge what it's doing.

96
00:23:04,044 --> 00:23:07,231
Worrying, worrying, planning, planning.

97
00:23:09,116 --> 00:23:14,549
And draw the attention away and bring it back to the breath and determine to stay there.

98
00:23:17,904 --> 00:23:43,608
feeling sleepy or tired just lift the spine open the eyes just a little and if the sleepiness is still there you can open them wide but keep the attention inward just relaxing the attention on the sensations caused by the breath allowing those neutral sensations to bring silence to the mind

99
00:23:44,247 --> 00:23:48,721
Calmness to the heart, stillness to the body.

100
00:25:58,926 --> 00:25:59,219
Thank you.

101
00:26:35,073 --> 00:26:41,839
If the mind is wandering, when you wake up out of it, really recognize and acknowledge what it is doing.

102
00:26:43,561 --> 00:26:49,268
We're interested in the mood, emotion, mental state or attitude that is driving the fantasies.

103
00:26:51,549 --> 00:26:52,790
Let go of the story.

104
00:26:53,392 --> 00:26:57,336
We're only interested in what is actually motivating it.

105
00:26:58,156 --> 00:27:01,941
Irritation, irritation, excitement, excitement.

106
00:27:03,237 --> 00:27:31,606
then draw the attention back to the breath and determine to stay there feeling sleepy or tired keep making that effort lifting up opening the eyes and don't forget if the dullness and lethargy become overwhelming you can stand up allowing the attention to settle on the breath as we feel more settled

107
00:27:32,329 --> 00:27:43,647
Draw yourself closer to see if you can catch the very beginning of the in-breath, stay with it to the very end, and the very beginning of the out-breath, and stay with it to the very end.

108
00:27:45,530 --> 00:27:53,763
If when you do this you find yourself getting tense, then sit back within yourself and have the impression of receiving the breath.

109
00:27:56,983 --> 00:28:02,386
Rising, rising, falling, falling.

110
00:30:47,067 --> 00:30:56,656
From now on, when the mind wanders and you recognize and acknowledge what's driving it, instead of coming back to the breath, come back into the body.

111
00:30:57,298 --> 00:30:58,439
See if you can feel it.

112
00:30:59,940 --> 00:31:03,984
If it is excitement, come into the body and see if you can feel the agitation.

113
00:31:05,605 --> 00:31:08,288
Feel the restlessness and perhaps heat of worry.

114
00:31:09,490 --> 00:31:12,012
If it's romance, feel the warmth and happiness.

115
00:31:13,875 --> 00:31:15,977
Stay there till it all evaporates.

116
00:31:17,797 --> 00:31:21,039
and again feeling dull-minded or lethargic in the body.

117
00:31:22,561 --> 00:31:26,766
You can also get into the feel of these states, the sensations, the feelings.

118
00:31:27,747 --> 00:31:31,971
Keep energizing the spine and you can still open the eyes to let the light in.

119
00:31:35,615 --> 00:31:38,698
When we get lost, we can always begin with the breath.

120
00:31:39,898 --> 00:31:42,320
The breath is our anchor and reference point.

121
00:31:43,803 --> 00:31:46,925
When we're confused, for instance, best to go back to the breath.

122
00:31:49,453 --> 00:31:51,258
Let's begin again with the breath.

123
00:31:52,821 --> 00:31:57,972
Rising, rising, falling, falling.

124
00:32:00,960 --> 00:32:05,589
And find the noting you need just to help keep the attention steady.

125
00:34:49,644 --> 00:34:54,311
Becoming aware of how we are reacting to what we're experiencing.

126
00:34:55,672 --> 00:34:58,936
How when something is pleasant, we're drawn towards it.

127
00:34:58,956 --> 00:35:01,199
We want to maintain it, to develop it.

128
00:35:02,422 --> 00:35:04,525
Can you feel the force of that desire?

129
00:35:06,447 --> 00:35:11,875
When something is unpleasant, we first ignore it, but then we just want to get rid of it.

130
00:35:12,576 --> 00:35:15,960
If the posture is a little uncomfortable, we want to change it.

131
00:35:17,202 --> 00:35:19,585
Can you feel the strength of the desire?

132
00:35:20,206 --> 00:35:23,291
Can you feel these desires and not do anything?

133
00:35:24,472 --> 00:35:28,719
Just allow them to express themselves and exhaust themselves.

134
00:35:32,266 --> 00:35:39,378
This is the desire the Buddha points to as the psychological cause for our suffering and unsatisfactoriness.

135
00:35:41,641 --> 00:35:42,702
Is that true for you?

136
00:38:27,451 --> 00:38:32,960
becoming aware of how everything we are experiencing is arising and passing away.

137
00:38:34,601 --> 00:38:36,144
Everything is in a process.

138
00:38:36,724 --> 00:38:37,907
Nothing repeats itself.

139
00:38:39,108 --> 00:38:41,853
Even though each breath is similar, they're never the same.

140
00:38:43,356 --> 00:38:45,179
Everything is vanishing, disappearing.

141
00:38:46,199 --> 00:38:47,101
Nothing remains.

142
00:38:49,605 --> 00:38:51,248
Is there anything reliable?

143
00:41:35,371 --> 00:41:39,976
Becoming more aware of how everything we're experiencing is an object.

144
00:41:41,980 --> 00:41:47,849
If we have discomfort in the knee, we're looking down from the position in the forehead as the observer.

145
00:41:48,969 --> 00:41:50,913
It's a sort of observation post.

146
00:41:53,036 --> 00:42:01,648
Can we make that separation, that distance between the observer, the feeler, the experiencer and the object more obvious to us?

147
00:42:03,079 --> 00:42:26,909
at times we can use a word like there so there's aching there over there is an itch if it's an emotion or mood in the body there's irritation there's excitement when it is an image in the mind right in front of you you can point to it there's an image you might even be able to do this with a thought

148
00:42:29,184 --> 00:42:38,483
Are the observer and the observed, the feeler and the felt, the experiencer and the experienced, the same or distinct?

149
00:42:41,791 --> 00:42:44,376
Can the perceiver be the perceived?

150
00:45:29,443 --> 00:45:34,230
becoming more aware of how everything is happening of its own accord.

151
00:45:36,052 --> 00:45:42,019
In avipassana, we've taken the objective position of the observer, the feel of the experiencer.

152
00:45:42,579 --> 00:45:48,907
We've separated out from the psycho-physical organism and allowed it to manifest as it wants.

153
00:45:50,489 --> 00:45:58,320
We find that the body offers us sensations and feelings, pleasant and unpleasant, whether we want it to or not.

154
00:45:59,835 --> 00:46:06,826
The heart, its moods and emotions, pleasant and unpleasant, whether we want it to or not.

155
00:46:08,708 --> 00:46:14,496
And the mind, its thoughts and images, wholesome and unwholesome, whether we want it to or not.

156
00:46:16,159 --> 00:46:18,021
We don't have direct control.

157
00:46:20,945 --> 00:46:29,438
If control is being exercised by the body, the heart and the mind, how can they be me?

158
00:49:14,742 --> 00:49:28,675
Putting aside all instruction, have absolute confidence that this intuitive awareness is able to understand the way things really are, that it can have profound insight into the nature of things.

159
00:49:29,536 --> 00:49:32,458
We don't need to keep thinking about it, prompting it.

160
00:49:33,239 --> 00:49:34,501
No need to do anything.

161
00:49:35,300 --> 00:49:36,902
Don't try and change anything.

162
00:49:37,963 --> 00:49:42,268
Just absolute acceptance of this is the way it is.

163
00:49:43,159 --> 00:49:52,797
All we need to do is just observe, just feel, just experience whatever draws the attention within the field of awareness.

164
00:52:37,342 --> 00:52:44,750
When we come to the end of a sitting, it's good to spend a little time reflecting on our experience.

165
00:52:44,769 --> 00:52:46,271
You can ask questions of yourself.

166
00:52:47,532 --> 00:52:51,277
How diligent was I in bringing myself back to the present moment?

167
00:53:02,547 --> 00:53:06,371
If I thought I was diligent, then I should congratulate myself.

168
00:53:07,380 --> 00:53:12,827
If I thought I could have been a little more committed, I should encourage myself.

169
00:53:13,286 --> 00:53:15,650
There's no need for self-criticism.

170
00:53:26,382 --> 00:53:30,306
Was there some mental state or physical state that you had to work with?

171
00:53:30,806 --> 00:53:33,630
Some form of discomfort or agitation perhaps?

172
00:53:35,331 --> 00:53:36,492
Some sleepiness?

173
00:53:37,655 --> 00:53:38,755
How did you deal with it?

174
00:53:39,556 --> 00:53:40,737
Just choose one of them.

175
00:53:54,393 --> 00:53:58,018
If you thought you were skillful, you can congratulate yourself.

176
00:53:59,619 --> 00:54:04,445
If you thought you could have been a little more committed, you could encourage yourself.

177
00:54:04,885 --> 00:54:07,088
Don't get into self-criticism.

178
00:54:19,960 --> 00:54:22,585
In this sitting, what was most prominent for you?

179
00:54:22,905 --> 00:54:26,632
The role of desire in creating unsatisfactoriness?

180
00:54:27,996 --> 00:54:29,800
Or was it the impermanence of things?

181
00:54:31,202 --> 00:54:37,394
Or was it that everything you were experiencing was an object, not under your direct control?

182
00:54:50,351 --> 00:54:51,954
And it's good to make a resolution.

183
00:54:52,835 --> 00:54:54,177
It can be quite specific.

184
00:54:55,179 --> 00:54:58,402
Next time I feel dozy, I'll immediately open my eyes.

185
00:54:59,784 --> 00:55:03,489
Or it can be a general commitment to affectionate mindfulness.

186
00:55:14,346 --> 00:55:17,009
When we come out of a sitting, don't jump out of it.

187
00:55:18,190 --> 00:55:19,632
Open the eyes gently.

188
00:55:20,304 --> 00:55:21,440
and let the light in.

